📱 iPhone Data Analysis on Flipkart - Project Overview

⬇️⬇️
🎯 This project focuses on analyzing iPhone listings on Flipkart to uncover trends in pricing, discounts, user ratings, and availability across different models. 
    By leveraging Python for data analysis, we aim to understand how iPhone prices fluctuate over time, the impact of sales events, and customer preferences.

📌 Objectives:
   *Analyze pricing trends for different iPhone models.
   *Identify discount patterns during Flipkart sales.
   *Examine user ratings and reviews for quality assessment.
   *Compare prices across different storage variants and colors.
   *Understand availability fluctuations based on demand.

🛠 Methodology:
   *Data Collection: Scraping iPhone listings from Flipkart.
   *Data Cleaning & Preprocessing: Handling missing values and formatting data.
   *Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA): Visualizing pricing trends, discounts, and customer preferences.
   *Statistical Insights: Identifying correlations between price drops, user ratings, and sales events.

📉 Technologies Used:
  🐍 Python (Pandas, NumPy) for data processing.
  📊 Data Visualization (Matplotlib, Seaborn, Plotly).
  📝 Jupyter Notebook for interactive analysis.

🔍 Key Insights & Business Value:
   This analysis helps customers make informed purchasing decisions, predicts best times to buy iPhones, and provides insights for retailers on pricing strategies and demand forecasting.
